implements java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>

Container and encoder for MultiPart/Form-data.

Initially constructed using information from section 17.13.4 of HTML 4.01 w3 specification ( http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/interact/forms.html#h-17.13.4.2).

Note. Please consult [RFC2388] for additional information about file uploads, including backwards compatibility issues, the relationship between "multipart/form-data" and other content types, performance issues, etc.

Example of use: 

  MultiPartFormDataEncoder formData = new MultiPartFormDataEncoder(); 
  this.formData.put("query", "Through the looking glass, Carrol, Lewis");
  this.formData.put("RecordSyntax", "marc");
  this.formData.put("Submit", "submit");
  String postRequestText = this.formData.encode();
